properties.areaDesc: Santa Ana Mountains and Foothills; Riverside County Mountains; San Bernardino County Mountains; San Gorgonio Pass Near Banning; San Bernardino and Riverside County Valleys-The Inland Empire
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 27 at 8:09PM PST until January 30 at 1:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North to northeast winds 20 to 35 mph, with gusts to 55
mph. Isolated gusts of 65 to 70 mph through canyons and in wind
prone foothill locations.

* WHERE...Along and below the coastal slopes of the mountains of
San Bernardino, Orange and Riverside Counties, and through
passes and canyons. Includes cities of Devore, Rialto, Rancho
Cucamonga, Portola Hills, Highland Springs.

* WHEN...From Wednesday morning through Thursday afternoon.
Strongest winds Wednesday evening into Wednesday night.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult, especially for high profile
vehicles. Damaging winds could blow down trees and power lines.
Widespread power outages are possible.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Difficult travel for high profile vehicles
especially along Interstate 15 through and below Cajon Pass,
Interstate 215 below Cajon Pass, and Interstate 10 through the
San Gorgonio Pass.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM WEDNESDAY MORNING THROUGH THURSDAY AFTERNOON
